Your Honor,

I stand before you today as a defendant who takes full responsibility for my actions. I plead guilty to the offense of speeding, as I drove my brand-new car without regard for the safety of those around me. I recognize the danger I posed and I deeply regret my reckless behavior.

I must admit that I was caught up in the thrill of experiencing the speed of my new car, and this clouded my judgment. However, I understand that my actions were inexcusable, and I acknowledge the seriousness of the offense.

Regarding the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP), I did not initially respond to it due to my negligence in handling my mail. It was not out of a deliberate intent to evade the consequences of my actions. If I had seen the notice, I would have taken immediate action to rectify my mistake. I acknowledge this as a significant factor in my guilt.

It is unfortunate that I already have penalty points on my license from previous speeding incidents. These incidents reflect my prior recklessness on the road. It is important to note that other than these driving offenses, I have had no record of criminal behavior.

Lastly, I want to express the genuine remorse I feel for the danger I created and the inconveniences I caused. I understand the gravity of my actions and the potential consequences they could have had.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I admit my guilt and take full responsibility for my actions. I sincerely regret my recklessness and the potential harm I caused. I humbly ask for your leniency and understanding. Thank you for your attention.

